             <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
               <m:mtext>
AB
               </m:mtext>
              </m:mrow>
             </m:mrow>
           </m:mrow>
          </m:msub>
         </m:mrow>
        </m:mrow>
       </m:mrow>
      
     </m:mrow>
     
    
   </m:math>  in magnitude. For a charge that is moved from plate A at higher potential to plate B at lower potential, a minus sign needs to be included as follows:  <m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">–Δ</m:mo>
                      <m:mi fontstyle="italic">V</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:msub>
                          <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                          
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mtext>A</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                          
                        </m:msub>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo>
                        <m:msub>
                          <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                          
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mtext>B</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                          
                        </m:msub>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                      
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mtext>AB</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                        </m:mrow>
                      
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
             
          </m:mrow>
        
      </m:math>. See the text for details.)</caption></figure><para id="import-auto-id2637761">The work done by the electric field in <link target-id="import-auto-id671952"/> to move a positive charge <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>q </m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> from A, the positive plate, higher potential, to B, the negative plate, lower potential, is</para>
    <equation id="eip-554"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mn>–Δ</m:mn><m:mtext>PE</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo><m:mi fontstyle="italic">q</m:mi><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id953198"> The potential difference between points A and B is</para>
    <equation id="eip-694"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">–Δ</m:mo>
                      <m:mi fontstyle="italic">V</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                      
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mtext>B</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                      
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                      
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mtext>A</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                      
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:msub>
                          <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                          
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mtext>A</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                          
                        </m:msub>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo>
                        <m:msub>
                          <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                          
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mtext>B</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                          
                        </m:msub>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                      
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mtext>AB</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                        </m:mrow>
                      
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
<m:mo>.</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
        
      </m:math> 
    </equation><para id="import-auto-id1059002">Entering this into the expression for work yields</para>
    <equation id="eip-217"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>W</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mtext fontstyle="italic">qV</m:mtext>
                        
                                <m:mtext>AB</m:mtext>
                        
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mrow>
<m:mo>.</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
          
        
      </m:math> 
    </equation><para id="import-auto-id1330624">Work is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">Fd</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>cos</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>; here <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>cos</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, since the path is parallel to the field, and so <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">Fd</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>. Since 
<m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>F</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">qE</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, we see that <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">qEd</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>. Substituting this expression for work into the previous equation gives</para><equation id="eip-725"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi fontstyle="italic">qEd</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">qV</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>AB</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id2543027">The charge cancels, and so the voltage between points A and B is seen to be</para><equation id="eip-537"><m:math>
