    </exercise>
    <exercise id="fs-id1563009" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2756439">    <para id="import-auto-id2721949">A doubly charged ion is accelerated to an energy of 32.0 keV by the electric field between two parallel conducting plates separated by 2.00 cm. What is the electric field strength between the plates?</para>
    </problem></exercise>
    <exercise id="fs-id1948894" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2677744">    <para id="import-auto-id2840049">An electron is to be accelerated in a uniform electric field having a strength of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>V/m</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>. (a) What energy in keV is given to the electron if it is accelerated through 0.400 m? (b) Over what distance would it have to be accelerated to increase its energy by 50.0 GeV?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2607322">
    <para id="import-auto-id2791118">(a) <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>800 KeV</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></para><para id="import-auto-id3166123">(b) <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>25.0 km</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></para></solution>
    </exercise>
